                  <summary>Account of arrears owed at the beginning of the 12th year of Claudius, in Philadelphia, for the poll tax, pig tax, and dike tax for the 11th, 9th, 8th, 7th and 6th years of the same reign. The economic crisis of these years was partly due to unusual Nile floods.</summary>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">See P.Mich. X, p. 66 for the number of defaulters which can be calculated from the amounts given on the papyrus: from ca. 57 defaulters for the poll tax of year 6 to ca. 635 defaulters for the same tax in year 7.</note>
